               <floruit notBefore="1604" notAfter="1623">He was a military
                  leader during the rule of 
                  <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos"><roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> </persName>
                . 
                  He attended at the first proclamation of <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos"/> as emperor at <placeName ref="LOC3788Harasm"/>. 
                 
                  In <date>1620</date><persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos"/> issued  a decree against the observance of Sabbath, but Yonāʾel refused to proclaim
                  it in the province of <placeName ref="LOC1713Bagemd"/>. Thereafter he waged an open rebellion against <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos"/>, opposing his pro-Jesuit policies.
                
                  </floruit>
                  <death notBefore="1622" notAfter="1623"/>
                  
